1
00:00:01,710 --> 00:00:03,628
<i>Stimulants, narcotics, cannabis.</i>

2
00:00:04,963 --> 00:00:07,132
<i>People who have used these drugs</i>

3
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:10,760
<i>are now estimated</i>
<i>to total two million in Japan.</i>

4
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:14,347
<i>The number of people arrested</i>
<i>for drug-related offenses</i>

5
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:17,142
<i>is as many as 14,000 yearly.</i>

6
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:20,311
Then get this over with quickly,

7
00:00:20,895 --> 00:00:22,188
police mutt.

8
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:23,398
Get lost,

9
00:00:24,232 --> 00:00:25,734
Ministry mutt.

10
00:00:25,817 --> 00:00:28,236
<i>You went off on your own again?</i>

11
00:00:28,319 --> 00:00:30,321
You can't just be biting at everything.

12
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:32,073
That's why they call you Mad Dog!

13
00:00:32,157 --> 00:00:33,825
<i>Become my "S."</i>

14
00:00:33,908 --> 00:00:35,452
<i>You're mad.</i>

15
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:37,370
You'll be my dog from today onwards.

16
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:39,080
Don't you care about your child?

17
00:00:39,164 --> 00:00:41,958
Don't just make shit up.

18
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:45,086
<i>He acts like a friendly,</i>
<i>upstanding guy on TV.</i>

19
00:00:45,170 --> 00:00:49,007
But they say he drugs women
and has his way with them.

20
00:00:49,591 --> 00:00:51,801
- Make him a customer.
- Seriously?

21
00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:54,929
Follow Matsubara's orders.
Meet Kaga and make him ingest cocaine.

22
00:00:55,013 --> 00:00:56,514
Get it on video.

23
00:00:56,598 --> 00:00:57,891
What?

24
00:00:57,974 --> 00:01:00,894
How would I know
where Kaga does his cocaine?

25
00:01:00,977 --> 00:01:05,273
<i>Plus, I'll get killed if Matsubara</i>
<i>finds out I'm connected to you!</i>

26
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:06,399
A Mad Dog!

27
00:01:06,483 --> 00:01:08,777
Doesn't that refer to Mr. Kurosaki?

28
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:11,029
<i>Kurosaki is the NCD's Mad Dog.</i>

29
00:01:11,112 --> 00:01:13,114
<i>Katsuragi is the police's Mad Dog.</i>

30
00:01:14,449 --> 00:01:17,285
Is this allowed?
For a cop to be this violent?

31
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:18,703
Shut the hell up!

32
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:21,790
What you've been trying
to attack all this time

33
00:01:22,665 --> 00:01:24,083
is the state's authority.

34
00:01:25,043 --> 00:01:28,421
You're a dead man.

35
00:01:34,135 --> 00:01:37,263
You're familiar with Hibiki Kaga,
a regional celebrity in Chiba?

36
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:39,098
The former boxer guy?

37
00:01:39,182 --> 00:01:41,518
He's on national TV too, occasionally.

38
00:01:41,601 --> 00:01:44,354
He's too timid on those
for his appeal to come through.

39
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:46,314
People in Chiba love him though.

40
00:01:46,397 --> 00:01:48,817
Who cares how well he does in Chiba?

41
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:52,570
- But he's Chiba's star!
- He's a star only in Chiba.

42
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:55,657
I get Chiba's TV channels
at my place here in Tokyo too.

43
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:58,660
You mean that Kaga?

44
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,328
Yeah, I mean that Kaga.

45
00:02:01,913 --> 00:02:05,208
Kurosaki's report says
that he's been using drugs recently.

46
00:02:05,291 --> 00:02:06,126
What?

47
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:12,215
Well, that's a surprise. I've never heard
any rumors of the sort about him.

48
00:02:12,298 --> 00:02:15,969
He's also suspected of making women
do drugs and have sex with him.

49
00:02:16,052 --> 00:02:19,931
Using his popularity to prey on women?
What a scumbag.

50
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:23,518
He should get on his knees
in front of every person in Chiba.

51
00:02:23,601 --> 00:02:25,103
As with Igarashi's incident,

52
00:02:25,186 --> 00:02:27,939
drug-related cases in showbiz
have been going up every year.

53
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:32,694
Capturing Kaga will make a big splash,
given his popularity with housewives.

54
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:35,989
Go find evidence and information
we can use to bring in Kaga.

55
00:02:36,072 --> 00:02:37,240
Yes, sir!

56
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:42,787
Isn't it likely that one of his victims
would be in a hospital for treatment?

57
00:02:42,871 --> 00:02:43,872
Good point.

58
00:02:43,955 --> 00:02:47,125
Aoshima, call every
single hospital in the city,

59
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:50,253
and ask if anyone came in
for drug-related treatment recently.

60
00:02:50,336 --> 00:02:51,296
Yes, sir.

61
00:02:54,382 --> 00:02:56,593
I'll get going then, sir.

62
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:58,112
<i>Listen well.</i>

63
00:03:58,196 --> 00:04:00,240
You'll pretend to be an S for the NCD,

64
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:02,617
and leak their information
to the police as an S for us.

65
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:05,495
- You mean like…
- A double agent.

66
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:07,455
What's in it for me?

67
00:04:07,538 --> 00:04:10,959
<i>I'll negate whatever dirt</i>
<i>Kurosaki has on you.</i>

68
00:04:11,459 --> 00:04:16,422
Think long and hard
about who you ought to side with.

69
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:21,678
The police or the NCD?

70
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:25,014
Every one of you keeps demanding
whatever you want.

71
00:04:26,641 --> 00:04:29,602
I don't care if it's the police
or the NCD, I'll be your damn S!

72
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:33,606
But just remember one thing.

73
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:39,487
Don't think you can tame me that easily.

74
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:47,412
Shit.

75
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:49,831
Mad bastard.

76
00:04:57,672 --> 00:04:59,716
And this guy too.

77
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,801
Has he no shame?

78
00:05:14,355 --> 00:05:17,775
Hey. Good job escaping the cops.

79
00:05:18,693 --> 00:05:20,361
Well, I got lucky.

80
00:05:20,445 --> 00:05:21,863
Good for you.

81
00:05:22,363 --> 00:05:24,407
You get to be free a while longer.

82
00:05:25,241 --> 00:05:26,576
Moving on.

83
00:05:26,659 --> 00:05:28,828
I've got another job for you.

84
00:05:30,371 --> 00:05:34,083
Kaga is being stalked by a woman
who he got hooked on drugs.

85
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:35,668
Snatch her.

86
00:05:36,252 --> 00:05:38,296
What? Why?

87
00:05:38,379 --> 00:05:41,924
Turns out that Kaga has connections
in the criminal world too.

88
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:43,801
He must have begged some higher-ups.

89
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:51,059
This is the insane stalker woman.

90
00:05:55,104 --> 00:05:56,773
If you do a decent job,

91
00:05:57,273 --> 00:05:59,942
consider your debt cleared.

92
00:06:01,235 --> 00:06:02,779
Wait, for real?

93
00:06:08,117 --> 00:06:09,368
Here.

94
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:12,413
- You're not joking, right?
- I'm not.

95
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:16,876
You've been asking for more recently.

96
00:06:18,169 --> 00:06:21,506
I get flamed online all the time
because of out-of-context articles,

97
00:06:21,589 --> 00:06:25,676
and shitty ignorant amateurs try
to lecture me on what I'm doing wrong.

98
00:06:26,177 --> 00:06:28,387
I need a way to unwind, you know?

99
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:32,600
Chiba's star sure is troubled.

100
00:06:38,898 --> 00:06:40,149
You trying to mock me?

101
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:44,987
Come on, don't start
lashing out at me too.

102
00:06:49,283 --> 00:06:50,409
Sorry.

103
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:54,997
To think she miscarried
even though you paid for the abortion.

104
00:06:55,748 --> 00:06:59,502
I would rather avoid any trouble,
so make sure you use condoms.

105
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:01,420
I know.

106
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:06,926
To users of speed and coke like us,
that kind of trouble is the worst.

107
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:16,185
The college student from before.

108
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:22,775
Hello, what's up?

109
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,445
Really?

110
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:28,281
<i>You feeling okay?</i>

111
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:34,954
I can't remember
most of what happened that day.

112
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:37,582
I didn't even drink that much.

113
00:07:37,665 --> 00:07:39,917
It's so weird.

114
00:07:40,001 --> 00:07:41,544
I see.

115
00:07:42,044 --> 00:07:44,172
How about we get dinner tonight?

116
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:45,590
What?

117
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:49,677
<i>There's a really good hot pot spot</i>
<i>I went to for a shoot recently.</i>

118
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:53,389
I'm sure you'll feel better
if you eat the hot pot there.

119
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:56,517
Okay.

120
00:07:56,601 --> 00:07:58,853
Call you later, then.

121
00:08:01,522 --> 00:08:04,525
Another case of addiction,
like it always goes?

122
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:23,586
Why are you drinking coffee
using a cup from someone else's home?

123
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:25,254
It's hot water.

124
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:26,714
Who cares?

125
00:08:28,883 --> 00:08:31,219
How did you get the police to release you?

126
00:08:32,428 --> 00:08:34,931
I threw the drugs down a drain as I ran.

127
00:08:35,431 --> 00:08:36,516
And then?

128
00:08:37,725 --> 00:08:41,437
I said I panicked and ran
after they said they were police.

129
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:44,857
So they released you
due to insufficient evidence?

130
00:08:45,441 --> 00:08:48,402
I see the police are as sloppy as always.

131
00:08:49,028 --> 00:08:51,030
Whatever. I have a mission for you.

132
00:08:51,113 --> 00:08:52,657
What, again?

133
00:08:53,157 --> 00:08:56,702
I'm still tired from the interrogation.
I didn't even get any sleep.

134
00:08:56,786 --> 00:08:57,787
Don't care.

135
00:08:58,287 --> 00:09:01,040
Hey, have you ever heard
of the Labor Standards Act?

136
00:09:01,123 --> 00:09:02,833
A criminal preaching law?

137
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:05,962
- Could you treat me any worse?
- I'll arrest you if you refuse.

138
00:09:06,045 --> 00:09:09,590
There you go with that again.
I'm done with this already.

139
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:11,425
Ow!

140
00:09:11,509 --> 00:09:12,593
Ouch!

141
00:09:12,677 --> 00:09:14,136
Not this again.

142
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:17,181
You will do as I tell you,
or you will get arrested.

143
00:09:17,265 --> 00:09:18,683
Don't make me repeat myself.

144
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:21,561
I get it. I'll do it.

145
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:23,145
That hurts.

146
00:09:24,272 --> 00:09:27,066
And? What do you want this time?

147
00:09:27,149 --> 00:09:29,068
Find the women Kaga is preying on.

148
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:30,403
What?

149
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:32,446
What's wrong?

150
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:35,283
Well, just a while ago…

151
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:39,370
Matsubara ordered me to kidnap this woman.

152
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:44,917
Kaga got her addicted,
and now, she's stalking him.

153
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:47,878
There are probably others
going after her too.

154
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:51,757
- What do they want with her?
- How would I know?

155
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:53,384
I was only given orders.

156
00:09:55,344 --> 00:09:57,638
Stick to Kaga and get dirt on him.

157
00:09:57,722 --> 00:10:00,349
He's filming at a shopping district
in Chiba today.

158
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:02,476
Really? Chiba?

159
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:04,478
That's so far.
I would have to go by train.

160
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:06,022
HIBIKI KAGA SCHEDULE

161
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:07,398
At least take me by car.

162
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:10,860
I'll go by myself. Wish me luck, sir!

163
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:14,572
On my way.

164
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:21,329
Fate is chosen by time,
realized by the heart,

165
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:24,540
and born when two souls
are attracted to each other.

166
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:26,626
I'm Hibiki Kaga.

167
00:10:27,126 --> 00:10:31,255
I smelled the fragrance of romance
from the flowers of this street corner.

168
00:10:31,339 --> 00:10:32,506
Catch, catch!

169
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:34,925
Let's go.

170
00:10:36,719 --> 00:10:40,348
Wait a second, take a look at this.

171
00:10:41,098 --> 00:10:45,561
The aura of these flowers is overpowering!

172
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:48,898
This shop is even more flowery than me!

173
00:10:49,398 --> 00:10:51,859
Let's take a closer look, shall we?

174
00:10:58,115 --> 00:11:00,368
I'm so sleepy, damn it.

175
00:11:01,952 --> 00:11:04,664
Do you get watered every day?

176
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:06,666
"Yes, I do."

177
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:08,834
Man, that sounds nice.

178
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:13,005
I wish someone would water me every day.

179
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:14,131
Catch!

180
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,301
- Good work today.
- Thanks.

181
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:18,886
We're done for the day.

182
00:11:18,969 --> 00:11:20,930
- Already?
- Yes. Thank you.

183
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:22,932
Oh, wow. Nice work today.

184
00:11:23,015 --> 00:11:24,308
That's a surprise.

185
00:11:24,392 --> 00:11:28,687
Can you really use that shot of me pulling
love fortune slips alone at the shrine?

186
00:11:28,771 --> 00:11:30,856
I must have looked like a loser there.

187
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:35,403
I think that will work great.
Should be relatable for lonely viewers.

188
00:11:35,486 --> 00:11:37,071
You serious?

189
00:11:37,154 --> 00:11:38,739
Hello?

190
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:40,866
The shoot is over. Can I go home now?

191
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:42,785
<i>He's likely to take action now.</i>

192
00:11:42,868 --> 00:11:45,538
<i>Keep tailing him</i>
<i>until you get something on him.</i>

193
00:11:46,455 --> 00:11:48,958
Will you at least pay for transportation?

194
00:11:51,085 --> 00:11:53,587
What the hell is his problem?

195
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:01,762
Eating out alone?

196
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,348
I doubt that.

197
00:12:07,643 --> 00:12:09,437
Oh, there you are.

198
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:15,276
Um…

199
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:20,781
What happened after we ate the sushi?

200
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:23,993
Wait, that's not her.

201
00:12:24,076 --> 00:12:27,538
I was alone in the hotel room
with no memory of how I got there.

202
00:12:29,331 --> 00:12:32,626
You said you felt unwell,
so I took you to a hotel.

203
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:33,878
You don't remember that?

204
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:38,674
The hot pot here is great.

205
00:12:38,757 --> 00:12:40,968
It will make you feel better for sure.

206
00:12:41,051 --> 00:12:42,678
Let's go in.

207
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:04,700
Can I go home already?
This work environment is too toxic.

208
00:13:04,783 --> 00:13:06,619
My head hurts too.

209
00:13:06,702 --> 00:13:08,537
And? Where's Kaga?

210
00:13:10,414 --> 00:13:13,167
Still inside with a woman
who's not the target.

211
00:13:14,376 --> 00:13:16,295
Oh, that's her.

212
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:22,343
- You go watch Kaga.
- What?

213
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:24,261
Hey! The heck?

214
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:52,790
Yes?

215
00:13:52,873 --> 00:13:54,625
You were right.

216
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:57,211
At Minato Sakura General Hospital,

217
00:13:57,294 --> 00:14:01,215
a woman with symptoms of drug addiction
was brought in this morning.

218
00:14:01,298 --> 00:14:03,801
The symptoms point to a cocaine addiction.

219
00:14:03,884 --> 00:14:06,303
Understood. I'll head there right away.

220
00:14:06,387 --> 00:14:08,681
<i>Be quick. Time is of the essence.</i>

221
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:20,359
- Where's Kaga?
- Still inside.

222
00:14:20,442 --> 00:14:21,902
- Get in.
- What?

223
00:14:26,156 --> 00:14:27,575
You in a hurry?

224
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:29,869
We found a woman Kaga got hooked on drugs.

225
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:30,786
What?

226
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:32,955
We'll get to her before the police.

227
00:14:33,038 --> 00:14:33,873
Okay.

228
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:53,601
It's this room.

229
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:00,316
No way.

230
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:02,359
I'll get a doctor.

231
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:09,533
Why?

232
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:26,634
Why…

233
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:33,849
Why!

234
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:39,605
Damn it!

235
00:15:39,688 --> 00:15:40,814
Why?

236
00:15:40,898 --> 00:15:42,858
Why the hell?

237
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:44,276
Shit.

238
00:15:45,486 --> 00:15:49,114
What the heck? Why are you crying?

239
00:15:49,907 --> 00:15:52,993
Isn't she just a stranger?

240
00:15:53,494 --> 00:15:56,205
It's just a drug addict who died.

241
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:02,544
Ouch!

242
00:16:03,045 --> 00:16:04,797
What's your problem?

243
00:16:08,842 --> 00:16:11,095
Try saying that again.

244
00:16:11,178 --> 00:16:12,554
What?

245
00:16:12,638 --> 00:16:13,931
I'll kill you.

246
00:16:14,014 --> 00:16:15,599
What are you getting worked up for?

247
00:16:17,601 --> 00:16:18,435
Get lost!

248
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:20,354
What's up with you?

249
00:16:20,437 --> 00:16:23,357
Always so self-centered.
You're the one who brought me--

250
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,483
Shut up!

251
00:16:24,566 --> 00:16:25,818
What is it with you?!

252
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:28,612
Have it your way!

253
00:16:52,886 --> 00:16:54,888
You're at fault too, you know.

254
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:57,141
What?

255
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:17,828
Remember it now?

256
00:17:19,455 --> 00:17:20,456
What?

257
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:22,624
Why?

258
00:17:23,292 --> 00:17:26,962
It would suck if this got
posted online, wouldn't it?

259
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:35,054
We used some drugs
and had a lot of fun together.

260
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:36,680
We're partners in crime.

261
00:17:37,598 --> 00:17:40,768
Now, let's eat while it's still soft.

262
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:07,419
Damn, my head hurts, and so does my face.

263
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:10,172
I can't sleep even though I'm sleepy.

264
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:14,676
How dare he punch me
after making me do all that work?

265
00:18:15,302 --> 00:18:17,054
Goddamn narcotics agent!

266
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:19,014
I'm gonna sleep again!

267
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:24,269
The woman took her life at the hospital.

268
00:18:24,353 --> 00:18:25,354
What?

269
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:28,565
According to Kurosaki, who discovered her,

270
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:32,694
she's undoubtedly someone
who got hooked on drugs due to Kaga.

271
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:35,489
What an absolute scumbag.

272
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:37,866
Filthy beast.

273
00:18:38,659 --> 00:18:39,743
Let's arrest him.

274
00:18:39,827 --> 00:18:41,578
We can get his urine with a warrant.

275
00:18:41,662 --> 00:18:44,206
As I'm sure you all already know,

276
00:18:44,706 --> 00:18:48,127
even if an autopsy reveals
traces of drugs in her system,

277
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:49,962
we don't know her relation to Kaga.

278
00:18:50,045 --> 00:18:52,965
Are you saying we can't do anything?

279
00:18:53,048 --> 00:18:54,133
Yes.

280
00:18:54,216 --> 00:18:57,469
We can't get a search warrant,
let alone an arrest warrant.

281
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:59,054
Shit.

282
00:18:59,763 --> 00:19:02,891
But we can't just let him
get away with this.

283
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:05,727
Are we going to let
scum like him roam free?

284
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:10,149
I'm with you. We have to keep
gathering evidence in secret for now.

285
00:19:10,649 --> 00:19:13,193
I ordered Kurosaki to do so as well.

286
00:19:13,277 --> 00:19:14,945
Where the heck is he?

287
00:19:20,284 --> 00:19:21,618
Hot!

288
00:19:22,202 --> 00:19:23,287
It's hot water.

289
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:24,496
Don't give me that!

290
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:26,540
Wait, this is illegal trespassing!

291
00:19:27,207 --> 00:19:30,961
Shut up. Don't hide behind the law
when you broke it, criminal scum.

292
00:19:31,879 --> 00:19:33,839
I can't handle this today.

293
00:19:33,922 --> 00:19:36,550
My head hurts
from getting too little sleep.

294
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:38,594
And that punch from you still hurts.

295
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:40,220
Let me get some sleep.

296
00:19:40,304 --> 00:19:42,848
Look. My eyelids are so heavy.

297
00:19:42,931 --> 00:19:44,349
Good night.

298
00:19:53,984 --> 00:19:54,985
What are these?

299
00:19:55,068 --> 00:19:57,196
Loxoprofen Sodium.

300
00:19:57,279 --> 00:19:58,530
That's some new drug?

301
00:19:58,614 --> 00:20:01,825
It's a painkiller.
Should take care of most kinds of pain.

302
00:20:01,909 --> 00:20:03,035
You sure about that?

303
00:20:03,118 --> 00:20:06,455
You don't get to question
the effects of medicine, scum.

304
00:20:06,538 --> 00:20:07,956
Chill, man.

305
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:09,708
I have a new mission for you.

306
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:12,669
Did you hear the part
about me not getting any sleep?

307
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:15,255
- Didn't you sleep yesterday?
- I couldn't!

308
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:17,799
My head hurts like it's being
smacked by a hammer.

309
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:20,594
Don't care! Your own fault
if you can't sleep at home.

310
00:20:20,677 --> 00:20:22,137
- You what?
- Just get dressed.

311
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:25,724
All right already.

312
00:20:26,642 --> 00:20:29,519
Oh, one thing though.

313
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:32,606
The woman from yesterday
had nothing to do with you, right?

314
00:20:33,106 --> 00:20:35,150
So why do you care so much?

315
00:20:35,234 --> 00:20:36,526
Not your business.

316
00:20:37,486 --> 00:20:41,365
Didn't expect
you would have that side to you.

317
00:20:42,950 --> 00:20:44,701
Ouch!

318
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:46,954
Shut up. Stop talking.

319
00:20:47,037 --> 00:20:48,288
I'll take down Kaga.

320
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:51,166
That's why I'm letting you roam free.

321
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:53,293
You just do as I tell you to.

322
00:20:54,002 --> 00:20:55,337
Get off me!

323
00:20:55,837 --> 00:20:57,047
That hurts.

324
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:00,092
What do I have to do?

325
00:21:00,926 --> 00:21:03,637
We can't act in the open without evidence.

326
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:06,807
My team is probably trying
to covertly gather evidence.

327
00:21:06,890 --> 00:21:09,268
But we're against time
when it comes to drugs!

328
00:21:09,351 --> 00:21:13,021
Another person could fall victim
while we stick to above-board methods.

329
00:21:14,856 --> 00:21:17,734
Remember the woman
at the hot pot place yesterday?

330
00:21:18,610 --> 00:21:19,444
Yeah.

331
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:21,571
Kaga could be feeding her cocaine,

332
00:21:21,655 --> 00:21:23,907
or potentially using her as a pawn.

333
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:25,784
Tail her.

334
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:27,953
About that,

335
00:21:28,620 --> 00:21:31,498
I have a bruise on my face
from you punching me.

336
00:21:32,165 --> 00:21:34,793
Don't you think I might draw attention?

337
00:21:35,335 --> 00:21:38,297
I will, won't I?
It's going to affect the mission!

338
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:41,466
I think it's a bad idea!
Don't you think it's a bad idea?

339
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:44,428
I bought makeup products.

340
00:21:44,928 --> 00:21:45,804
What?

341
00:21:46,346 --> 00:21:48,849
You were an actor, right?
Hide it with makeup.

342
00:21:50,142 --> 00:21:52,102
You bought way too much.

343
00:21:56,064 --> 00:21:59,609
You said to tail her,
but where even is she?

344
00:22:21,548 --> 00:22:22,507
A GPS tracker?

345
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:24,843
She's at her home right now.

346
00:22:24,926 --> 00:22:27,095
- Isn't this a crime?
- So what?

347
00:22:27,179 --> 00:22:29,139
I have my own methods.

348
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:32,434
You really are mad.

349
00:22:32,934 --> 00:22:37,397
She's a college student named
Aoi Sugihara, from what I could find.

350
00:22:37,898 --> 00:22:39,483
If we keep track of her,

351
00:22:39,566 --> 00:22:42,486
we'll uncover Kaga's
true colors soon enough.

352
00:22:44,279 --> 00:22:45,489
Hey!

353
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:50,160
What's his problem?

354
00:22:52,579 --> 00:22:54,915
Screw that! I'm not taking this!

355
00:22:54,998 --> 00:22:57,918
I won't let him get his way.

356
00:23:00,754 --> 00:23:02,464
Hello, Umezawa here.

357
00:23:03,507 --> 00:23:06,468
I met with that shitty Kurosaki
from the NCD just now.

358
00:23:06,968 --> 00:23:08,345
I have some info.

359
00:23:09,012 --> 00:23:09,930
Do you want it?

360
00:23:12,307 --> 00:23:14,476
I didn't expect a call
from you this quick.

361
00:23:15,727 --> 00:23:17,938
Quite useful, aren't you?

362
00:23:25,487 --> 00:23:28,281
<i>Kaga told her to come</i>
<i>to a club in Roppongi tonight.</i>

363
00:23:28,365 --> 00:23:29,366
<i>Sneak in.</i>

364
00:23:29,449 --> 00:23:30,325
<i>What?</i>

365
00:23:30,408 --> 00:23:33,829
You think they'll just let me
into such a crazy party that easily?

366
00:23:33,912 --> 00:23:36,164
I didn't say to go in as a guest.

367
00:23:36,748 --> 00:23:39,918
As long as the rule
of law exists in Japan,

368
00:23:40,001 --> 00:23:42,587
we have to prioritize
optics above all else!

369
00:23:42,671 --> 00:23:45,257
Screw that! You're just trying
to cover your own ass!

370
00:23:45,340 --> 00:23:47,968
- You really a dealer?
- If you get high…

371
00:23:48,051 --> 00:23:49,219
KAGA CORNERS HIM

372
00:23:49,803 --> 00:23:52,347
<i>I'll buy enough for everyone here.</i>

373
00:23:52,430 --> 00:23:54,224
Goddamn it!

374
00:23:54,933 --> 00:24:00,856
ANY RESEMBLANCE TO ACTUAL PERSONS, GROUPS,
OR CASES IS PURELY COINCIDENTAL

375
00:24:00,939 --> 00:24:01,898
Subtitle translation by: Saim Ul Hassan
